Applied Valuation and Risk Management
<b>
<b>March 20-22, 2002 - San Diego, CA
<b> 
<b>Evaluate Wholesale Derivative Energy Contracts, Experiment with the relationship between value and risk in your portfolio, and the implications of price
<b> volatility in power and fuel markets.
<b>
<b>Click here for a complete workshop brochure.
<b>http://www.mailbag.com/users/welsh/evr.htm
<b>
<b>What Past Participants Have Said		
<b>This scenario-based training gives you hands-on experience solving problems in energy risk management and valuation of contracts and assets.  Participants will work through problems that include:
<b>
<b>*	Finding and using forward price curves
<b>*	Estimating volatility
<b>*	Embedded options: valuing and pricing complex contracts
<b>*	Valuing "full requirements" obligations
<b>*	Real options: valuing generating resources
<b>*	Designing and testing hedging strategies
<b>
<b>This course is designed for professionals who are responsible for risk management, power supply planning, fuel planning, retail services, energy trading/marketing, treasury, corporate finance and corporate strategy.
<b>
